# Cloudflare Pages — _redirects
# Catch-all: return true 404 for any path not matching a deployed file.
# This fixes the soft-404 issue documented in docs/site-os/qa/2026-05-18-soft-404-catch-all.md
# where Cloudflare Pages was serving the homepage (200 OK) for every unmatched URL.
#
# IMPORTANT: This file must live in the repo root (or the Cloudflare Pages publish directory).
# Cloudflare Pages evaluates _redirects AFTER static file matching, so built pages
# are served normally — only truly unmatched paths hit this rule.
#
# Rule format: [source] [destination] [status]

/springtail-exterminator-las-vegas/  /false-chinch-bug-exterminator-las-vegas/  301
/las-vegas-valley/sunrise-manor/     /pest-control-sunrise-manor-nv/            301
/* /404.html 404
